Cook,  <br><br>
If you ever want to know a song that describes the sixties and the seventies -- it might take a search -- it's a rendition of Herbie Mann's version of HOLD ON I'M COMING by Sam and Dave.  It was on an album of his called MEMPHIS UNDERGROUND.  It's the drug song on that era and it &quot;tells&quot; how the world was on the edge.<br><br>
